{
  "answer": "**I could not find any couplet by Mirza Ghalib in the Falsafa corpus that uses the specific images of \"the candle's tongue\" and \"the moth's prayer\" (or close equivalents like *shama ki zubaan* and *parwane ki dua*).**\n\nGhalib's *Diwan-e-Ghalib* (239 ghazals) frequently employs the moth (*parwana*) and candle/flame (*shama*/*aatish*) as classic metaphors for love's self-destructive passion.[^1][^2][^3][^4] For example:\n\n- \"Asad, consumed by waiting's restless, burning might, / A moth before the flame of sacred light was.\"[^5]\n- \"We shed our wings like moths consumed by fire.\"[^6]\n- \"The moth's own heart is spring itself, so practice flight again.\"[^7]\n- \"what love demands is a moth's wing to feed its own desire.\"[^8]\n\nHowever, extensive searches across English translations for phrases like \"candle's tongue,\" \"moth's prayer,\" \"tongue\" near candle/flame, or \"prayer\" near moth/*parwana* yielded no matches. The corpus covers the full *Diwan*, but these exact images do not appear in the available translations.\n\nIf this refers to a specific *sher* known by those English terms, it may use different wording here or be from another collection not in the Falsafa corpus (37 works total).\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [Chapter 51](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/51-gham-nahin-hota-hai-aazaadon-ko-besh-az-yak-nafas/translation/).\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [Chapter 4](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/04-aaina-dekh-apna-sa-munh-le-ke-reh-gaye/translation/).\n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [Chapter 63](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/63-hai-sabza-zaar-har-dar-o-deewar-e-gham-kada/translation/).\n[^4]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [Chapter 64](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/64-hai-vasl-hijr-aalam-e-tamkeen-o-zabt-mein/translation/).\n[^5]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [p-d266ce](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/04-aaina-dekh-apna-sa-munh-le-ke-reh-gaye/translation/#p-d266ce).\n[^6]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [p-5a393a](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/51-gham-nahin-hota-hai-aazaadon-ko-besh-az-yak-nafas/translation/#p-5a393a).\n[^7]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [p-62afc5](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/63-hai-sabza-zaar-har-dar-o-deewar-e-gham-kada/translation/#p-62afc5).\n[^8]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [p-f5c9ca](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/64-hai-vasl-hijr-aalam-e-tamkeen-o-zabt-mein/translation/#p-f5c9ca).",
